    specialFilter([15, -73, 14, -15]) => 1 
    specialFilter([33, -2, -3, 45, 21, 109]) => 2
    """
Code  :
import math

def specialFilter(nums):
    count = 0
    for num in nums:
        if math.floor(num / 10) % 2 == 1 and math.floor(num % 10) % 2 == 1:
            count += 1
    return count
