    and where the leading non-zero entry makes a solution likely.
    >>> round(locate_root([1, 2]), 2) # f(x) = 1 + 2x
    -0.5
    >>> round(locate_root([-6, 11, -6, 1]), 2) # (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) = -6 + 11x - 6x^2 + x^3
